ernal text" href="//www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=11939">11939</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANon-convexity+%28economics%29&amp;rft.atitle=A+synthesis+of+pure+demand+analysis+II&amp;rft.aufirst=Herman&amp;rft.aulast=Wold&amp;rft.date=1943&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Skandinavisk+Aktuarietidskrift+%5BScandinavian+Actuarial+Journal%5D&amp;rft.pages=220-263&amp;rft.volume=26&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fmathscinet-getitem%3Fmr%3D11939&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span>\n<p>Exercise 45, page 146: <cite id="CITEREFWoldJur.C3.A9en1953" class="citation book"><a href="/wiki/Herman_Wold" title="Herman Wold">Wold, Herman</a>; Jur\xc3\xa9en, Lars (in association with Wold) (1953). "8 Some further applications of preference fields (pp.&#160;129\xe2\x80\x93148)". <i>Demand analysis: A study in econometrics</i>. Wiley publications in statistics. New York: John Wiley and Sons,&#160;Inc. Stockholm: Almqvist and Wiksell. pp.&#160;xvi+358. <a href="/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews" title="Mathematical Reviews">MR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=64385">64385</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANon-convexity+%28economics%29&amp;rft.atitle=8+Some+further+applications+of+preference+fields+%28pp.+129%E2%80%93148%29&amp;rft.au=Jur%C3%A9en%2C+Lars+%28in+association+with+Wold%29&amp;rft.aufirst=Herman&amp;rft.aulast=Wold&amp;rft.btitle=Demand+analysis%3A+A+study+in+econometrics&amp;rft.date=1953&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.pages=xvi%2B358&amp;rft.place=New+York&amp;rft.pub=John+Wiley+and+Sons%2C+Inc.+Stockholm%3A+Almqvist+and+Wiksell&amp;rft.series=Wiley+publications+in+statistics&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fmathscinet-getitem%3Fmr%3D64385&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></p>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-14"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-14">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFSamuelson1950">Samuelson (1950</a>, pp.&#160;359\xe2\x80\x93360):</span>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class="reference-text">It will be noted that any point where the indifference curves are convex rather than concave cannot be observed in a competitive market. Such points are shrouded in eternal darkness\xe2\x80\x94unless we make our consumer a monopsonist and let him choose between goods lying on a very convex "budget curve" (along which he is affecting the price of what he buys). In this monopsony case, we could still deduce the slope of the man\'s indifference curve from the slope of the observed constraint at the equilibrium point.</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n<span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFSamuelson1950" class="citation news"><a href="/wiki/Paul_Samuelson" title="Paul Samuelson">Samuelson, Paul&#160;A.</a> (1950). "The problem of integrability in utility theory". <i>Economica (New Series)</i>. <b>17</b>. pp.&#160;355\xe2\x80\x93385. <a href="/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews" title="Mathematical Reviews">MR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=43436">43436</a>. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.2307%2F2549499">10.2307/2549499</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANon-convexity+%28economics%29&amp;rft.atitle=The+problem+of+integrability+in+utility+theory&amp;rft.aufirst=Paul+A.&amp;rft.aulast=Samuelson&amp;rft.date=1950&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Economica+%28New+Series%29&amp;rft.pages=355-385&amp;rft.volume=17&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fmathscinet-getitem%3Fmr%3D43436&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.2307%2F2549499&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span>For the <a href="/wiki/Epigraph_(literature)" title="Epigraph (literature)">epigraph</a> to their seventh chapter, "Markets with non-convex preferences and production" presenting <a href="#CITEREFStarr1969">Starr (1969)</a>, <a href="#CITEREFArrowHahn1971">Arrow &amp; Hahn (1971</a>, p.&#160;169) quote <a href="/wiki/John_Milton" title="John Milton">John Milton</a>\'s description of the (non-convex) <a href="/wiki/Serbonian_Bog" title="Serbonian Bog">Serbonian Bog</a> in <i><a href="/wiki/Paradise_Lost" title="Paradise Lost">Paradise Lost</a></i> (<a href="https://en.wikisource.org/wiki/Paradise_Lost_(1674)/Book_II" class="extiw" title="s:Paradise Lost (1674)/Book II">Book&#160;II, lines&#160;592\xe2\x80\x93594</a>):</span>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A gulf profound as that Serbonian Bog<br /></p>\n<p>Betwixt Damiata and Mount Casius old,<br /></p>\nWhere Armies whole have sunk.</blockquote>\n</li>\n<li id="cite_note-Diewert-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Diewert_15-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="#CITEREFDiewert1982">Diewert (1982</a>, pp.&#160;552\xe2\x80\x93553): <cite id="CITEREFDiewert1982" class="citation book">Diewert, W.&#160;E. (1982). "12 Duality approaches to microeconomic theory". In <a href="/wiki/Kenneth_Arrow" title="Kenneth Arrow">Arrow, Kenneth&#160;Joseph</a>; Intriligator, Michael&#160;D. <i>Handbook of mathematical&#160;economics, Volume&#160;<b>II</b></i>. Handbooks in economics. <b>1</b>. Amsterdam: North-Holland Publishing&#160;Co. pp.&#160;535\xe2\x80\x93599. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-444-86127-6" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-444-86127-6">978-0-444-86127-6</a>. <a href="/wiki/Mathematical_Reviews" title="Mathematical Reviews">MR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.ams.org/mathscinet-getitem?mr=648778">648778</a>. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1016%2FS1573-4382%2882%2902007-4">10.1016/S1573-4382(82)02007-4</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANon-convexity+%28economics%29&amp;rft.atitle=12+Duality+approaches+to+microeconomic+theory&amp;rft.aufirst=W.+E.&amp;rft.aulast=Diewert&amp;rft.btitle=Handbook+of+mathematical+economics%2C+Volume+II&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-444-86127-6&amp;rft.pages=535-599&amp;rft.place=Amsterdam&amp;rft.pub=North-Holland+Publishing+Co.&amp;rft.series=Handbooks+in+economics&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.ams.org%2Fmathscinet-getitem%3Fmr%3D648778&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2FS1573-4382%2882%2902007-4&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li>\n<li id="cite_note-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-16">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Farrell, M.&#160;J. (August 1959). "The Convexity assumption in the theory of competitive markets". <i><a href="/wiki/The_Journal_of_Political_Economy" class="mw-redirect" title="The Journal of Political Economy">The Journal of Political Economy</a></i>. <b>67</b> (4): 371\xe2\x80\x93391. <a href="/wiki/JSTOR" title="JSTOR">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.jstor.org/stable/1825163">1825163</a>. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1086%2F258197">10.1086/258197</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ANon-convexity+%28economics%29&amp;rft.atitle=The+Convexity+assumption+in+the+theory+of+competitive+markets&amp;rft.aufirst=M.+J.&amp;rft.aulast=Farrell&amp;rft.date=1959-08&amp